Well I just gave upon some old games, haha
yeah, some games are like time capsules, nice to visit but dated and tough to tolerate.
just stepping stones on a road to modern game design~
Marathon 1 I *kinda* gave a pass because eventually I could find what I needed, even if it was infuriating
Like a secret door in an "elevator" that would crush you if you didn't find it.
The only way you'd know it was there was if you paid attention to the map shown during the mission debriefing, and noticed that the room on your map didn't match up
Spam interact at roughly the right spot and *woosh*, new passageway!
But if you failed... get your butt sent back to the last save you have, which would be on the previous level, and you'd have to recomplete whatever you were doing to finish that level up.
But once I got to the first level where the air mechanic comes into play?  Nope, sorry.  I'm out.  Ain't dealing with that only 7 levels into a 25+ level game.
